<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 13 at 2:43PM EDT  by NWS Pittsburgh</headline>
<description>...AN AREA OF MODERATE TO HEAVY SNOW WILL AFFECT NORTHEASTERN
MERCER...VENANGO... NORTHEASTERN INDIANA...NORTHEASTERN
BUTLER...JEFFERSON...NORTHERN ARMSTRONG...CLARION AND FOREST
COUNTIES...
At 243 PM EDT, an area of heavy snow was located along a line
extending from near Greenville to 7 miles west of Northern Cambria.
Movement was east at 40 mph.
Locations impacted include...
Oil City, Franklin, Punxsutawney, Clarion, Brookville, Marienville,
Knox, Rimersburg, Greenville, Sugarcreek, Reynoldsville, and
Brockway.
This includes the following highways...
Interstate 79 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 123 and 137.
Interstate 80 in Pennsylvania between mile markers 26 and 96.
Visibilities will drop quickly to less than a quarter of a mile in
this area of heavy snow.</description>
